Kursus annab ülevaate peamistest inimese tunnetust ja käitumist suunavatest ja reguleerivatest teguritest spordi ja muude oskuste meisterlikule sooritamisele orienteeritud valdkondade kontekstis. Käsitletakse tunnetuspsühholoogia peamisi valdkondi (tähelepanu, mälu, õppimine, mõtlemine), emotsioonide ja motivatsiooni seoseid, inimese arengut ja individuaalseid erinevusi, grupiprotsesse ja juhendamist ning eestvedamist, psühholoogiliste oskuste treenimise aluseid, liikumisega seotud tervisekäitumist ja sooritust takistavaid tegureid. Teemade käsitlemisel lähtutakse liigutusoskuste omandamise ja reguleerimise seisukohalt olulistest probleemidest.
 	This course provides an overview of the main factors that regulate human cognitive and behavioral processes in sport and other fields oriented to mastering performance skills. Main issues of cognitive psychology (attention, memory, learning, thinking), associations between emotions and motivation, human development and individual differences, group processes, instruction, and leadership, bases of psychological skills training, exercise-related health behavior, and factors inhibiting performance are focused on. Aspects relevant for understanding the acquiring and regulating motor skills are accentuated.Objectives/eesmärkid:  After the course, students will be able to identify psychological and social processes related to mastering and performing athletic and other speciality skills, and to integrate those processes in the context of development, leadership, well-being, and health.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students will be able to 1.	describe a wide range of topics covered by sport and performance psychology 2.	demonstrate a basic understanding of research methods and design in sport and performance psychology 3.	analyses biological, developmental, motivational, social, and environmental factors affecting the development of skills and expertise.  4.	explain psychological processes affecting performance and describes their interrelations in the context of performance 5.	understand the modes of action of factors inhibiting the development of performance skills and hindering skill mastering, and relate prospects to reducing the risk factors 6.	demonstrate understanding of how physical activity influences mental health and well-being 7.	design plans for habit development
